    <title type="text">Mandaean Gnostic Texts Online</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/about/">Brian Mubaraki</a>
      is developing the site <a href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/">Mandaean Gnosticism:
      research, publications and debate</a>, where he is providing access to pdfs of Mandaic
      texts.<br /><blockquote><span style="font-size:85%;"><a
      href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/publications/">...</a> In the early part of the
      1990′s, while at university, I embarked on creating a set of Mandaic computer fonts with the
      aim of reproducing the then hand written or microfilmed surviving Mandaic texts into printed
      format. The printed format has marked advantages over the handwritten texts including easy
      editing, clearer more consistent and reproducible text. In 1998 we completed the reproduction
      of the <em>Ginza Rba</em>, to my knowledge, at the time this was the first work of
      its kind. Today, my work with the reproduction of the Mandaic publications continues – without
      the associated noise, the back slapping or pomp and ceremony of my contemporaries.</span>
      <p><span style="font-size:85%;">In the following pages I have provided PDF copies
      of the Mandaic texts reproduced thus far. These texts are available in other formats both
      electronic and hardcopy. Please contact me if more information is required<a
      href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/publications/">...</a></span></p><ul
      class="children"><li class="page_item page-item-156"><span
      style="font-size:78%;"><a href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/publications/diwans-scrolls/"
      title="Diwans (Scrolls)">Diwans (Scrolls)</a></span></li><li
      class="page_item page-item-90"><span style="font-size:78%;"><a
      href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/publications/ginza-rba/" title="Ginza Rba">Ginza
      Rba</a></span></li><li class="page_item page-item-146"><span
      style="font-size:78%;"><a href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/publications/qulasta/"
      title="Qulasta">Qulasta</a></span></li><li class="page_item
      page-item-168"><span style="font-size:78%;"><a
      href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/publications/rasta/"
      title="Rasta">Rasta</a></span></li><li class="page_item
      page-item-133"><span style="font-size:78%;"><a
      href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/publications/transliterated-ginza-rba/" title="Transliterated
      Ginza Rba">Transliterated Ginza Rba</a></span></li><li class="page_item
      page-item-165"><span style="font-size:78%;"><a
      href="http://yardna.wordpress.com/publications/transliterated-qulasta/" title="Transliterated
      Qulasta">Transliterated
      Qulasta</a></span></li></ul></blockquote><p></p><br
